23 3. The Superintendent of Public Instruction shall:
24 (a) Establish an application process through which a pupil
25 may request to attend, pursuant to paragraph (f) of subsection 2, a
26 public school outside the zone of attendance that the pupil is
27 otherwise required to attend. The process must:
28 (1) Include an annual deadline by which a pupil must
29 submit the application to the board of trustees of the school district
30 in which the school the pupil requests to attend is located; and
31 (2) Provide for the notification of a pupil and his or her
32 parent or legal guardian, and the principals of the schools
33 involved in the transfer of the pupil, if an application is approved.
34 (b) On the Internet website maintained by the Department,
35 annually publish data describing, for pupils who transferred
36 between schools located in different zones of attendance pursuant
37 to paragraph (f) of subsection 2:
38 (1) The total number of pupils who transferred between
39 schools located in different zones of attendance during the
40 previous school year; and
41 (2) For each public school, the number of pupils who
42 transferred into and out of the school pursuant to paragraph (f) of
43 subsection 2 during the previous school year.
44 4. The board of trustees of each school district shall:
