1 (a) Establish capacity limits for each grade level within each
2 public school in the school district.
3 (b) Require a public school in the school district to enroll a
4 pupil whose application submitted pursuant to subsection 3 has
5 been approved, so long as the public school has capacity at the
6 grade level of the pupil.
7 (c) Establish a method to determine which pupils to enroll in
8 any grade level within a public school for which applications
9 exceed the capacity limits established pursuant to paragraph (a),
10 which may include, without limitation, a lottery system.
11 (d) Allow a pupil whose application submitted pursuant to
12 subsection 3 has been approved to permanently transfer to that
13 public school without requiring an additional application in any
14 subsequent school year.
15 (e) Prepare and submit an annual report to the Superintendent
16 of Public Instruction describing:
17 (1) The number of applications received pursuant to
18 subsection 3 and the number of such applications that were
19 approved or denied; and
20 (2) For each application that was denied, the reason the
21 board of trustees of the school district denied the application.
22 5. The application process established pursuant to subsection
23 3 must prohibit the consideration of any of the following factors in
24 determining whether to approve an application:
25 (a) The academic, artistic or athletic ability of a pupil;
26 (b) The participation of a pupil in any extracurricular activity
27 or the skill of a pupil in such an activity;
28 (c) Whether a pupil is a pupil with a disability;
29 (d) Whether a pupil is an English learner;
30 (e) The address at which the pupil resides; or
31 (f) Except as otherwise provided in this paragraph, whether a
32 pupil has previously been subject to any disciplinary action. The
33 board of trustees of a school district may deny the application of a
34 pupil who, in the school year for which the application is
35 submitted or in the immediately preceding school year, was
36 suspended for 10 or more days or expelled.
37 6. If an application to attend a public school outside the zone
38 of attendance that a pupil is otherwise required to attend submitted
39 pursuant to subsection 3 is denied or no action is taken on the
40 application, the parent or legal guardian of the pupil may appeal
41 the denial or lack of action to the superintendent of the school
42 district and, if he or she upholds the decision of the board of
43 trustees of the school district, to the Superintendent of Public
44 Instruction. The Superintendent of Public Instruction shall
